gt; Floops<br>Plat Ruby Veil &gt; Velium<br>BIM &gt; BAM<br>Velium RIngs<br>Kromriff Leggings<br>RMB/Hammer bracer<br>Shroud of Nature<br>First few shawl quests to get a seal or thordian <p><left><font face=arial color=black size=2><b> <BR><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=69903">Milwein Fenrir</A>Druid of the 57th Ring <BR>Proud Member of <A HREF="http://www.tkagiro.com">T`Kagi Ro</A><BR> Fennin Ro Server </left>  <center>  <BR> "Never argue with an idiot. <BR> They drag you down to their level then beat you with experience." </font></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubalise.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Balise</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/11/02 10:39:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26381.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Equipment Upgrade Help</span><hr size=1> Runed Circlet from Perma, at 29 you should be able to solo it.  Not a huge upgrade, but better then Sevants Cap and not hard to get.  You have pretty good equip already for that leavel, just get up to mid 40's and you can upgrade the rest. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=47458><b>Balise</b></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ujentrikenaspenbark.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jentriken Aspenbark</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/12/02 4:47:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26381.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Equipment Upgrade Help</span><hr size=1> a paw of opolla in main hand would be helpful too. <p>Venerable Jentriken Aspenbark<BR><BR>Retired Heirophant of Xegony</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usaereajaciabre.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Saere Ajaciabre</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_yellowspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/12/02 5:57:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26381.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Equipment Upgrade Help</span><hr size=1> How about a blackened iron medallion?  It's 5ac, 5wis and a focus effect.  :)  You can either try and purchase one, but since it now has a focus you may be better off going and getting one on your own, you will need a group since it drops in RE from Battlewizard Uzak.  G'luck!<br><br>Sae <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/urayvin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rayvin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/12/02 7:53:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26381.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> BAM</span><hr size=1> Saere, what you're thinking of is a Black Alloy Medallion, and they drop off of the Battlewiz, Battlelord, Lord Pickclaw, and supposedly a couple other more common mobs (Slayspells and Destroyers).  I got one off of the lordy yesterday, yellow to me at 31, the rest are dark blues.  I have soloed and grouped in Runnyeye for the past week, most of the time soloing or duoing with a warrior or monk.  The grouping is definitely preferable as the gobs go down much faster.  When solo, I usually invis up, run down to the bank (skin/coat/str/sow outside, of course), shield of brambles, and start pulling one or two at a time.  No harmony (indoors), but if you plan it out you can single pull at least from the area around the fountain next to the bank.  I bind myself to the Gorge zone next to the entrance to Runnyeye, that way if I get too many adds I can root them and gate out, then invis back in without much delay.  I can usually take out a DB and a LB using only 3 bubbles of mana, then retreat to the bank, hide or invis (important! NOTE: the banker will aggro on you if you sit while visible in the bank!).  Rinse, repeat!  Oh, watch out for the Zekspeakers (GHeal, and through walls) and the Slayspells (didn't notice one of these, and it started nuking me continuously when I healed my partner... it's very hard to see over the tables and chairs as a halfling, lol... took to sitting on the tables pretty quickly).<br><br>Rayvin al'Canis<br>Lvl 31 Druid of the Vale<br>The original, only 150 Wis<br>Cazic-Thule <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.showPrevMessage?topicID=26381.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.showNextMessage?topicID=26381.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26381.topic&index=5><img src=http://www.execpc.com/~msippel/thedruidsgrove/images/addreply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.emailToFriend?topicID=26381.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard